As APC Chairmanship aspirants round off consultations with barely five days to the party Convention, Governor Inuwa Yahaya of Gombe State has said that they deserve the best to manage the party and take it to the next level. The governor spoke when one of the leading APC Chairmanship aspirants, Senator Sani Musa paid him a courtesy visit in continuation of his consultation to leaders of the All Progressives Congress (APC). The Governor who spoke extensively on ways to move the party forward used the occasion to commend his visitor for offering himself to serve the party and Nigeria. Governor Inuwa Yahaya stated that the All Progressives Congress (APC) in all sincerity of purpose deserves the best hand to manage its affairs at this time and expressed his conviction that Senator Musa possesses the right leadership qualities for the role he is aspiring. Yahaya, however, urged the aspirant to intensify ongoing consultation while wishing him well. Presenting his agenda for the party if elected as the national chairman, Senator Sani Musa disclosed that he was fully prepared to bring about a visionary leadership to the APC and rejig the entire party architecture in line with international best practices.